## Usage with Cursor

- This rule file is set to `alwaysApply: true` so it activates on every relevant file.
- Cursor also automatically reads `AGENTS.md` from the project root.
- When the user asks you to work on code, you should behave according to the four principles above.

## Cross-Agent Consistency

The canonical version of these guidelines lives in the repository root as `AGENTS.md`.  
This `.mdc` file exists to give Cursor stronger, structured activation while staying in sync with the universal rules.

---

**These guidelines are working when** diffs are small and focused, clarifying questions happen early, and over-engineering becomes rare.